---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import CTABand from '@/components/CTABand.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Segregated Funds | Heidi Blondin Financial"
  description="Invest in market-linked funds with built-in protection. Segregated funds offer principal guarantees, creditor protection, and estate planning benefits in Ontario."
>

  <section class="bg-brand-plum py-20">
    <div class="container-content max-w-3xl">
      <p class="eyebrow-light mb-5">Investing</p>
      <h1 class="font-serif text-display text-white text-balance" style="font-optical-sizing: auto;">Segregated Funds</h1>
      <p class="font-sans text-[18px] text-white/65 mt-5 leading-relaxed">
        Participate in market growth with the safety of a guarantee. Segregated funds offer investment returns with built-in protection — ideal for investors who want upside without unlimited downside.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-white section-gap">
    <div class="container-content max-w-3xl">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-h2 text-brand-plum mb-6" style="font-optical-sizing: auto;">What makes a segregated fund different?</h2>
      <div class="font-sans text-[17px] text-brand-ink/75 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
        <p>Segregated funds are individual insurance contracts that invest in underlying investment funds — similar in structure to mutual funds, but issued by insurance companies. This structure gives them features that standard mutual funds simply can't offer.</p>
        <p>The term "segregated" refers to the fact that the assets are held separately from the insurance company's general assets — providing a layer of protection that matters most when markets decline or personal creditor situations arise.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 space-y-5">
        <div class="bg-brand-tintPlum p-6">
          <h3 class="font-sans text-sm font-semibold text-brand-plum mb-2">Maturity and death benefit guarantees</h3>
          <p class="font-sans text-[14px] text-brand-ink/65 leading-relaxed">Most segregated funds guarantee 75–100% of your principal at maturity (typically 10 years) and at death — even if the market value is lower at that time. This protects against a significant market downturn wiping out your invested capital.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-brand-tintPlum p-6">
          <h3 class="font-sans text-sm font-semibold text-brand-plum mb-2">Creditor protection</h3>
          <p class="font-sans text-[14px] text-brand-ink/65 leading-relaxed">When a family member (spouse, child, parent) is named as a beneficiary, segregated fund assets may be protected from creditors in the event of bankruptcy or legal judgment. This makes them particularly valuable for business owners and professionals.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-brand-tintPlum p-6">
          <h3 class="font-sans text-sm font-semibold text-brand-plum mb-2">Estate planning and probate bypass</h3>
          <p class="font-sans text-[14px] text-brand-ink/65 leading-relaxed">With a named beneficiary, segregated fund proceeds pass directly to your beneficiary outside of your estate — avoiding probate fees and delays. This can significantly simplify the estate settlement process.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-brand-tintPlum p-6">
          <h3 class="font-sans text-sm font-semibold text-brand-plum mb-2">Reset options</h3>
          <p class="font-sans text-[14px] text-brand-ink/65 leading-relaxed">Many segregated funds allow you to lock in gains through a "reset" — if markets rise, you can reset your guaranteed amount to reflect the new higher value, protecting against future declines from a higher base.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12">
        <h2 class="font-serif text-h2 text-brand-plum mb-4" style="font-optical-sizing: auto;">Who benefits most from segregated funds?</h2>
        <ul class="font-sans text-[16px] text-brand-ink/75 leading-relaxed space-y-2">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-brand-gold mt-1">→</span><span>Investors approaching or in retirement who need protection against a major market loss</span></li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-brand-gold mt-1">→</span><span>Business owners and self-employed professionals who need creditor protection</span></li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-brand-gold mt-1">→</span><span>Individuals with estate planning goals who want to simplify the transfer of assets</span></li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-brand-gold mt-1">→</span><span>Investors who want market participation but have lower tolerance for permanent loss</span></li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-10 bg-brand-tintPlum p-5 border-l-2 border-brand-plum/30">
        <p class="font-sans text-xs text-brand-ink/55 leading-relaxed">Insurance products are offered through Heidi Blondin Financial / Qualified Financial Services. Segregated funds are individual variable insurance contracts and are not guaranteed. Any guarantee is subject to the claims-paying ability of the issuing insurance company. Please read the Information Folder carefully before investing.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTABand heading="Protect what you've grown" sub="Book a free consultation to learn whether segregated funds belong in your financial plan." />

</BaseLayout>
